description: It is a world much like our own-and a world in the throes of great change, shaken by the appearance of individuals that are more than human. The first of these new humans was Jeff Carey-who decided to use his abilities for the betterment of mankind. Because of this choice, his family was taken from him, murdered by his enemies. Now, he's been reborn as a figure of darkness and revenge. Now, he is trapped inside a maximum security prison with an army of killers-many of whom he put there. Or are they trapped inside with HIM? Be there for the shocking climax-and learn his true objective in storming the prison single-handed! Plus: How did he get his powers in the first place?

He's lost everything-his wife and daughter, his wealth and fame, his status as a hero. But there is still one connection to Jeff Carey's past left, one which may hold the key to his past and future! With the help of the mysterious stranger he freed from a maximum-security prison, the reasons for the murder of Jeff's family become clearer - as do the clues that will help him track down the killers and make them pay. But even as he edges closer to redemption, his faceless enemies edge closer to him.

For months, since the murder of his family, Jeff Carey has known only loneliness, despair, and anger. But now, he's found an ally--someone who may be able to help him find answers about the past they share. But while they seek the truth, the last criminal that was touched by the man once called Paragon hunts them. As the conspiracy begins to coalesce, it becomes apparent that Melanie--Jeff's only companion for many months--may hold the key to everything.

Having freed his father from decades-long confinement, the secret of Jeff Carey's powers has been revealed? But that truth only leads to greater danger and a web of conspiracy. Now father and son are re-united to hunt the killers who murdered Jeff's family. But they are about to encounter someone who may have the power to destroy them both? And who has a very large axe to grind with Jeff...

The explosive conclusion to the first story arc! Jeff and his father have traced the group responsible for the deaths of Jeffs family to remotest Africa. There, Jeff is faced by the one man who may be his equal and who could prevent him from discovering the horrible truth behind the lives and deaths of his family! When the smoke clears, Jeff Carey and the Aftermath world will never be the same again

Acclaimed writer/artist Ashley Wood takes on the world of street-racing as only he can. In this two-part tale, enter a world of illegal drag-racing, where the vehicles aren't cars at all... instead, they're robots with minds and motivations of their own. Pumping pistons, crazed characters, and cool sneakers await you in Duo Stars. And each issue will be adorned by two Wood covers, too!
